A Landrover ferrying 16 people to Maralal town on Saturday morning was involved in an accident after it lost control, killing the driver instantly.The 6am incident occurred in Nomotio area on the Maralal Loosuk road.Fifteen passengers were seriously injured and have been admitted at Samburu County Referral Hospital.Area OCPD Abagoro Guyo said the driver lost control as the vehicle was going downhill and failed to negotiate a sharp corner."The brakes failed as the vehicle was going downhill," Abagaro told journalists.He said motorists should avoid using personal cars as public service vehicles.Residents also asked government authorities to erect bumps on the road to contain speeding by drivers.